  "texts": [
    "α t: This is the modulating factor that adjusts the weight of the loss for each sample according to its class.",
    "It aids in balancing the influence of easy and difficult samples.",
    "γ: This parameter that controls the rate at which the modulating factor decreases with increasing predicted probability.By incorporating Focal Loss, the model can allocate more attention to samples that are difficult to classify, thereby diminishing the influence of simpler samples.",
    "This, in turn, enhances the model's performance on minority classes.",
    "The parameters α t and γ of Focal Loss can be adjusted according to the specific requirements of the task."
  ],
